	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-09-22T05:01:00">The Henderson Smaller Companies Investment Trust plc is a United Kingdom-based investment trust company. The Company's investment objective is to maximize shareholders' total returns by investing mainly in smaller companies that are quoted in the United Kingdom. The Company's principal activity is investing in shares and securities. The Company invests in a range of industry sectors, such as general industrials, finance-general, consumer services, healthcare, technology, consumer goods, materials, and oil and gas. The wholly owned subsidiaries of Henderson Group plc (Henderson) provide investment management, accounting, secretarial and administrative services to the Company. Henderson Investment Funds Limited (HIFL) is the alternative investment fund manager of the Company.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-02-13T06:44:11">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 November 2015, Henderson Smaller Companies Inv Trst PLC revenues decreased 67% to -L5.3M. Net loss increased 37% to L7.7M. Revenues reflect Gain on Investments held at FV through P decrease of 33% to -L11.3M, Other Income decrease of 88% to L14K. Higher net loss reflects Other Expenses increase of 9% to L252K (expense). Dividend per share remained flat at L0.04.</Text>
